-- Lloyds Banking Group sells UK commercial real estate loan portfolio
-- 
-- Thu Jun 05, 2014 02:12AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, June 5 (Reuters) - Lloyds Banking Group <LLOY.L> has sold a portfolio of UK commercial real estate loans to Promontoria Holding, an affiliate of Cerberus Global Investors, for 352 million pounds ($589.72 million).

In a statement on Thursday, the bank said the transaction, which it expects to complete in the second half of 2014, involves assets of 536 million pounds which generated a 17 million pounds loss in 2013.